notes.en:
There are five types of noun suffixes in Klingon.

Noun Type 1: Augmentative/diminutive
▶ {-'a':n:suff}
▶ {-Hom:n:suff}
▶ {-oy:n:suff}

Noun Type 2: Number
▶ {-pu':n:suff}
▶ {-Du':n:suff}
▶ {-mey:n:suff}

Noun Type 3: Qualification
▶ {-qoq:n:suff}
▶ {-Hey:n:suff}
▶ {-na':n:suff}

Noun Type 4: Possession/specification
▶ {-wIj:n:suff} / {-wI':n:suff}
▶ {-lIj:n:suff} / {-lI':n:suff}
▶ {-Daj:n:suff}
▶ {-maj:n:suff} / {-ma':n:suff}
▶ {-raj:n:suff} / {-ra':n:suff}
▶ {-chaj:n:suff}
▶ {-vam:n:suff}
▶ {-vetlh:n:suff}

Noun Type 5: Syntactic markers
▶ {-Daq:n:suff}
▶ {-vo':n:suff}
▶ {-mo':n:suff}
▶ {-vaD:n:suff}
▶ {-'e':n:suff}

The joke goes like this:

▶ {Doq'a' SuvwI'pu'?:sen:nolink}
  "Are warriors red?"

▶ {ghobe'. SuD.}
  "No. They are green."

Watch a lesson on this joke: {YouTube video:url:http://youtu.be/HciuEJSpPq0}

