Examples of special forms of this construction (all from [3]):
▶ {tlhIngan woch law' tera'ngan woch rap.:sen:nolink} "The Klingon is as tall as the Terran."
▶ {tlhIngan woch law' tera'ngan woch nIb.:sen:nolink} "The Klingon is (exactly) as tall as the Terran."
▶ {ro'qegh'Iwchab 'ey law' qagh 'ey law'.:sen:nolink} "The rokeg blood pie is as delicious as the gagh." (Deliciousness is a positive quality when applied to food.)
▶ {'Iw HIq bIr puS chuch bIr puS.:sen:nolink} "The bloodwine is as cold as the ice is", "the bloodwine is as cold as ice." (Coldness is considered a negative quality when applied to bloodwine, which is best served warm.)
▶ {QuchlIj vIl law' QuchwIj vIl pIm.:sen:nolink} "Your forehead is not as ridgy as my forehead." (This does not imply "My forehead is ridgier than yours", only that they are not the same in ridginess.)
▶ {QuchwIj vIl law' QuchlIj vIl puS.:sen:nolink} "My forehead is ridgier than your forehead."
▶ {QuchlIj vIl law'be' QuchwIj vIl puSbe'.:sen:nolink} "Your forehead isn't ridgier than my forehead."
▶ {jIH Doy' law' SoH Doy' puS.:sen:nolink} "I am more tired than you are."

Examples of similes (all from [3]):
▶ {SuvwI' ghung law' qagh ghung rap.:sen:nolink} "The warrior is as hungry as gagh." (from {ghung; qagh rur})
▶ {tlhIngan HoS law', 'Iw HoS law'.:sen:nolink} "The Klingon is as strong as blood." (from {HoS; 'Iw rur})
▶ {verengan puj puS, bIQ puj puS.:sen:nolink} "The Ferengi is as weak as water." (from {puj; bIQ rur})

Examples of quantified comparisons (both from [5]):
▶ {cha' DISmo' jIH qan law' SoH qan puS:sen:nolink} "I'm two years older than you."
▶ {cha' 'ujmo' jIH woch law' SoH woch puS:sen:nolink} "I'm two {'uj:sen}es taller than you."

The following example shows that the verb of quality can take a suffix:
▶ {SoH rallaw' law' Hoch rallaw' puS.:sen:nolink}[4]

