notes.en:
The joke goes like this:

▶ {'avwI'vaD jatlh qama'; jIghung.}
  "A prisoner says to the guard: 'I am hungry.'"

▶ {jang 'avwI'; jIghung je.}
  "The guard replies: 'I am also hungry.'"

▶ {jatlh qama'; jI'oj.}
  "The prisoner says: 'I am thirsty.'"

▶ {jang 'avwI'; jI'oj je.}
  "The guard replies: 'I am also thirsty.'"

▶ {jatlh qama'; jIDoy'qu'.}
  "The prisoner says: 'I am very tired.'"

▶ {jatlh 'avwI'; jIDoy'be'.}
  "The guard says: 'I am not tired.'"

This is the opening line of a drinking song. The lyrics are not grammatical in modern standard Klingon, since they are ancient:
▶ {'ej HumtaH 'ej DechtaH 'Iw:sen:nolink}
   {'ej Doq SoDtaH ghoSpa' SIqral bIQtIq:sen:nolink}
   {'e' pa' jaj law' mo' jaj puS:sen:nolink}
   {jaj qeylIS molor mIgh HoHchu'qu':sen:nolink}
  "And the blood was ankle deep
   And the River Skral ran crimson red
   On the day above all days
   When Kahless slew evil Molor dead!"

The plural of this pronoun is {bIH:n:pro}.

