▶ {SoH:n}:{'oH:n:nolink} = {Da-:v:pref}
▶ {tlhIH:n}:{'oH:n:nolink} = {bo-:v:pref}
▶ {ghaH:n}/{'oH:n:nolink}:{'oH:n:nolink} = {0:v:pref}
▶ {chaH:n}/{bIH:n}:{'oH:n:nolink} = {lu-:v:pref}

The imperative verb prefix when {'oH:n:nolink} is the object is {yI-:v:pref}.

examples.en:
▶ {qIvo'rIt pagh'e':sen:nolink}
   {qIvo'rIt toQDuj 'oH tlhIngan wo' Duj pagh'e'. ra' qarghan HoD. DujvamDaq tlhIngan nuH tu'lu'bogh pov law' Hoch pov puS 'ej DujvamDaq 'op SuvwI' tu'lu'bogh po' law' tlhIngan yo' SuvwI' law' po' puS.:sen:nolink}
  "K'Vort Class Pagh
   The Imperial Klingon Vessel Pagh is a K'Vort-class Bird-of-Prey under the command of Captain Kargan. It has the best weapons and some of the finest warriors in the Klingon fleet."[2]

▶ {qeylIS loDnI':sen:nolink}
   {'opleS chovan:sen:nolink}
   {tuqmaj vIDevmo':sen:nolink}
  "One day, brother Kahless,
   You will bow for me
   As leader of our house."[1]

▶ {toDuj 'oS rol.:sen}
▶ {qorDu'Daj tuq 'oS Ha'quj'e' tuQbogh wo'rIv.:sen:nolink} "The sash that Worf wears is a symbol of his family's house."[2]
▶ {yay 'oS bey.:sen:nolink} "This yell is victorious in nature."[3]

▶ {'oy'naQ:sen:nolink}
   {nentay loptaHvIS tlhIngan potlh tlhIngan 'oy'naQ'e'. SIQwI' lu'oy'moHmeH juppu'Daj 'oy'naQmey lo' chaH. SuvwI' qa' patlh veb chavlaHmeH tlhIngan lo'chu' chaH. toDujDaj toblu'. wej 'ujmey 'ab 'oy'naQ. chIch vay' 'oy'moHmeH 'oy'naQ 'ul law' tlhuD 'oH.:sen:nolink}
  "Painstik
   The Klingon Painstik is an important part of a Klingon's Age of Ascension ceremony. The Painstik is employed by friends of the recipent who use the devices to inflict pain in a manner which will allow the Klingon to attain a higher state of spirituality as a warrior, proving his mettle. Painstiks are a little over one meter long and emit a highly-charged shock for the express purpose of inflicting pain."[2]

▶ {nuv 'umHa' leghchugh veqlargh:sen:nolink}
   {ngoS nuv 'umHa':sen:nolink}
   {net jatlh:sen:nolink}
  "Those unfit disintegrate
   At the glance of Fek'lhr,
   So it is said."[1]

notes.en:
This is the empty verb prefix. Following the notation in {TKD:src}, it is denoted by {0:v:pref,nolink} here.

{ghaH:n}/{'oH:n}:{pagh:n:1h} = {0:v:pref,nolink}
{ghaH:n}/{'oH:n}:{ghaH:n}/{'oH:n} = {0:v:pref,nolink}
{ghaH:n}/{'oH:n}:{chaH:n}/{bIH:n} = {0:v:pref,nolink}
{chaH:n}/{bIH:n}:{pagh:n:1h} = {0:v:pref,nolink}
{chaH:n}/{bIH:n}:{chaH:n}/{bIH:n} = {0:v:pref,nolink}

Note that the prefix for "they-him/her/it" is {lu-:v:pref}.

