notes.en:
This is the opening monologue of {DSC:src}, spoken by {tIquvma:n:name}:
▶ {ghoSlI' chaH.:sen:nolink}
   {ngIq HeySelmaj'e' nuSev 'ej nuqat:sen@@ngIq:n, HeySel:n, -maj:n, -'e':n, nu-:v, Sev:v, 'ej:conj, nu-:v, qat:v:1}
   {'ej nutaHmoHbogh Hoch lunge'.:sen@@'ej:conj, nu-:v, taH:v:1, -bogh:v, Hoch:n, lu-:v, nge':v}
   {buQwI'vam 'omlu'meH wa' mIw tu'lu';:sen@@buQ:v, -wI':v, -vam:n, 'om:v, -lu':v, -meH:v, wa':n, mIw:n, tu'lu':v}
   {wo'majDaq ghobtaHbogh cha'maH loS tuqmey DItay'nISqa'moH.:sen@@wo':n, -maj:n, -Daq:n, ghob:v, -taH:v, -bogh:v, cha'maH:n, loS:n:1, tuq:n, -mey:n, DI-:v, tay':v, -nIS:v, -qa':v, -moH:v}
   {loD lIjlaHbe'bogh vay' wIlIjpu' -:sen@@loD:n, lIj:v, -laH:v, -be':v, -bogh:v, vay':n, wI-:v, lIj:v, -pu':v}
   {tuqmeymaj tay'moHmeH qeylIS'e':sen@@tuq:n, -mey:n, -maj:n, tay':v, -moH:v, -meH:v, qeylIS:n, -'e':n}
   {wa' qangtlhIn wIpab;:sen@@wa':n, qangtlhIn:n, wI-:v, pab:v} {tlhIngan maH! taHjaj!:sen}
   {nuvma' DIghommoHmeH, DaHjaj rI'meH qulmaj wIchu'.:sen@@nuv:n, -ma':n, DI-:v, ghom:v, -moH:v, -meH:v, DaHjaj:n, rI':v, -meH:v, qul:n, -maj:n, wI-:v, chu':v:2}
   {jagh wI'ommeH pe'vIl DeSDu'maj DIrar.:sen@@jagh:n, wI-:v, 'om:v, -meH:v, pe'vIl:adv, DeS:n:1, -Du':n, -maj:n, DI-:v, rar:v}
   {HeghmoHbogh rI'meH mu'meyvam jatlh jaghma'...:sen@@HeghmoH:v, -bogh:v, rI':v, -meH:v, mu':n, -mey:n, -vam:n, jatlh:v, jagh:n, -ma':n}
  "They are coming.
   Atom by atom... they will coil around us...
   and take all that we are.
   There is one way to confront this threat.
   By reuniting the 24 warring Houses of our own empire.
   We have forgotten the Unforgettable...
   the last to unify our tribes - Kahless -
   together, under one creed... remain Klingon!
   That is why we light our beacon this day. To assemble our people.
   To lock arms against those whose fatal greeting is..."

The speech concludes with the words (in Federation Standard): "We come in peace."

